  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Las Pavas community&apos;s capacity and improving their food security</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conduct training and coordinate knowledge Exchange workshops on land rights and sustainable farming processes. Promote collective farming practices within the community to reduce household expenses, improve crop diversification and increase household incomes. Workshops to strengthen ASOCAB&apos;s organisational capacity from a gender perspective. Carry out an updated assessment of the community&apos;s nutritional needs. Identify and promote varieties of produce that will meet the nutritional needs of the community. Construction of 8 Deep water Wells to increase access to water. Provision of seeds and agricultural inputs, tools and supplies. Provision of technical agricultural advice to improve productivity and market access. Coordinate capacity building and awareness raising workshops with women initially focusing on women&apos;s rights and inclusion. Provide ongoing technical support, supplies and equipment for women to develop economically sustainable ventures such as productive fruit orchards.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To reachs families within the association who haven&apos;t yet been reached, whilst strengthening the capacity of ASOCAB to defend their land. The project will also seek to improve the inclusiveness of ASOCAB and strengthen women&apos;s position in the community more broadly (at present there are no women in the decision-making body, and female members&apos; points of view are not taken into account).</narrative>
  </description>
